caption: Food is decently edible BUT low review is because of delivery (direct), which seems to be reoccurring. They state ASAP delivery within 40 minutes. After waiting over an hr called to see if the food has left the store and if did then when. They stated the delivery was made. The deliverer stated they left it at the front desk and I was "called" (did NOT). Asked front desk and they mentioned they asked the deliverer for the apt but deliverer only said they already called, again did NOT.  After reading other reviews, even after giving a generous tip beforehand, this situation was outrageous.

Food is decent but the main reason for the low review is because of delivery service (direct). On their site it states ASAP delivery is within 40 minutes, which seems amazing BUT apparently it's NOT. After waiting over an hr called the store and they stated that their deliverer had just returned from the delivery. They stated the food was already delivered a while ago and I was "called" (did NOT) because they were stopped at the front desk. Front desk asked for the apt # (was not labeled on the food) but deliverer stated they already called, again did NOT.

I really loved their food the other night and was excited to order again today. While the restaurant was great the delivery process has caused me to never want to order from here again. I ordered online and forgot to tip on the card. Honest mistake. I don't have cash at the ready these days because of covid.  I ordered eggs benedict and a smoothie. When the order arrived at my apartment, I opened it up and the eggs benedict sauce was everywhere in the bag and no longer in the dish.  I called the restaurant and they offered very kindly to fix it right away, which was great. But they sent the same delivery guy who TOLD me he shook it because I didn't tip him before and wouldn't leave until I did.  Never ordering from here again. I'd consider coming in for pickup but the delivery process was completely rude, you never know what a person is going through and maybe they can't afford something, if this has been a different person this could have led to a more significantly bad situation.

I placed a order for pick up for a teriyaki bowl and a side of roasted brussel sprouts. What a mistake! The brussel sprouts were raw and I was at work so I couldn’t even pop them in the oven to eat them. The teriyaki bowl (carrots, zucchini, caramelized onions, broccoli sautéed with ginger-teriyaki glaze) had 3 cubes of zucchini and 2 pieces of broccoli and was soaked in the glaze (no hint of ginger) and didn’t have any onions. I could and actually have made a better bowl myself!! All of this for $18 - not worth it at all. When I called to express my frustration about my meal, the manager who answered, while he did offer to make me something new (which I was not interested in because I couldn’t see how another option would be good if they serve something like this) was then rude, didn’t even apologize and hung up on me!  Will not be returning.
